| P4-G | Self-hosted Ollama provider (local/LAN/reverse proxy) | вң… |', '{dev,workflow,procedural}', 'public', 'system', '2026-04-28 00:00:00+00', '2026-04-29 00:00:00+00', '', 'human', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.950, 0.950, 1.000, 0.950, 0.900, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'active', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.memory_nodes (id, schema_version, workspace_id, title_zh, title_en, content_type, content_format, body_zh, body_en, tags, visibility, author, created_at, updated_at, signature, source_type, source_document, extraction_model, copied_from_node, copied_from_ws, trust_score, dim_accuracy, dim_freshness, dim_utility, dim_author_rep, votes_up, votes_down, verifications, traversal_count, unique_traverser_count, status, archived_at, embedding, validity_confirmed_at, validity_confirmed_by, source_file) VALUES ('mem_d002', '1.0', 'ws_spec0001', 'Edgeпјҡжңүеҗ‘жңүеһӢзҡ„й—ңдҝӮ', 'Edge: a typed, directed relationship', 'factual', 'markdown', 'Edge йҖЈжҺҘе…©еҖӢ Memory NodeпјҢж–№еҗ‘зӮә `from вҶ’ to`гҖӮжҜҸжўқ Edge еҢ…еҗ«пјҡ

- **Relation type**пјҡdepends_on / extends / related_to / contradicts
- **Weight**пјҡ0вҖ“1пјҢеҸҚжҳ й—ңдҝӮеј·еәҰпјӣз”ұ decay иҲҮ co-access boost еӢ•ж…Ӣжӣҙж–°
- **Co-access count**пјҡиў«е…ұеҗҢеӯҳеҸ–зҡ„ж¬Ўж•ё
- **Decay еҸғж•ё**пјҡhalf_life_daysпјҲй җиЁӯ 30пјүгҖҒmin_weightпјҲй җиЁӯ 0.1пјү
- **Traversal**пјҡиө°иЁӘж¬Ўж•ёгҖҒе№іеқҮи©•еҲҶпјҲ1вҖ“5пјүгҖҒи©•еҲҶдәәж•ё

Edge ID ж јејҸпјҡ`edge_<hex8>`гҖӮеҗҢдёҖе°ҚзҜҖй»һй–“зӣёеҗҢ relation type зҡ„ Edge дёҚйҮҚиӨҮгҖӮ', 'An Edge connects two Memory Nodes with direction `from вҶ’ to`. Each edge contains:

- **Relation type**: depends_on / extends / related_to / contradicts
- **Weight**: 0вҖ“1, reflecting relationship strength; dynamically updated by decay and co-access boost
- **Co-access count**: how many times accessed together
- **Decay parameters**: half_life_days (default 30), min_weight (default 0.1)
- **Traversal**: visit count, average rating (1вҖ“5), rating count

Edge ID format: `edge_<hex8>`. Duplicate edges (same from, to, relation) are rejected.', '{data-model,schema,graph,core}', 'public', 'memtrace-spec', '2026-04-11 00:00:00+00', NULL, 'e5f6a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b2c3d4e5f6', 'human', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.950, 0.950, 1.000, 0.950, 0.900, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 'active', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.memory_nodes (id, schema_version, workspace_id, title_zh, title_en, content_type, content_format, body_zh, body_en, tags, visibility, author, created_at, updated_at, signature, source_type, source_document, extraction_model, copied_from_node, copied_from_ws, trust_score, dim_accuracy, dim_freshness, dim_utility, dim_author_rep, votes_up, votes_down, verifications, traversal_count, unique_traverser_count, status, archived_at, embedding, validity_confirmed_at, validity_confirmed_by, source_file) VALUES ('mem_1fc8782f', '1.0', 'ws_spec0001', 'иЁҳжҶ¶зҜҖй»һиӢұж–Үе…§ж–Ү', 'Memory Node English Body', 'factual', 'markdown', '`memory_nodes` иЎЁдёӯзҡ„ `body_en` ж¬„дҪҚйЎһеһӢзӮә TEXTпјҢеӯҳе„ІиЁҳжҶ¶зҜҖй»һзҡ„иӢұж–ҮжӯЈж–ҮгҖӮ', 'The `body_en` column in the `memory_nodes` table is of type TEXT, storing the English body of the memory node.', '{database,schema,memory_nodes,column,i18n}', 'public', 'system', '2026-04-24 11:25:38.987893+00', NULL, '38def61e607255d825e41054e1ef73f9bbe01b69d8df3be4d7d18a59eb8e41ac', 'ai', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.715, 0.800, 1.000, 0.500, 0.500, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'active', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.memory_nodes (id, schema_version, workspace_id, title_zh, title_en, content_type, content_format, body_zh, body_en, tags, visibility, author, created_at, updated_at, signature, source_type, source_document, extraction_model, copied_from_node, copied_from_ws, trust_score, dim_accuracy, dim_freshness, dim_utility, dim_author_rep, votes_up, votes_down, verifications, traversal_count, unique_traverser_count, status, archived_at, embedding, validity_confirmed_at, validity_confirmed_by, source_file) VALUES ('mem_d004', '1.0', 'ws_spec0001', 'Trust зі»зөұпјҡдҝЎд»»еҰӮдҪ•иў«иЁҲз®—', 'Trust system: how trust is calculated', 'factual', 'markdown', 'жҜҸеҖӢ Memory Node её¶жңүдёҖеҖӢ 0вҖ“1 зҡ„з¶ңеҗҲдҝЎд»»еҲҶж•ёпјҢз”ұеӣӣеҖӢз¶ӯеәҰеҗҲжҲҗпјҡ

| з¶ӯеәҰ | иӘӘжҳҺ | е»әз«ӢжҷӮй җиЁӯ |
|------|------|----------|
| `accuracy` | дәӢеҜҰжӯЈзўәжҖ§ | 0.5 |
| `freshness` | жҷӮж•ҲжҖ§ | 1.0 |
| `utility` | еҜҰз”ЁзЁӢеәҰ | 0.5 |
| `author_rep` | дҪңиҖ…дҝЎиӯҪ | 0.5 |

дҝЎд»»еҲҶж•ёйҡЁзӨҫзҫӨжҠ•зҘЁпјҲup/downпјүиҲҮй©—иӯүж¬Ўж•ёжҢҒзәҢжӣҙж–°гҖӮе…§е®№д»Ҙ SHA-256 з°Ҫз« йҳІеҒҪпјҢжҜҸж¬Ўе„ІеӯҳйҮҚж–°иЁҲз®—гҖӮTrust score < 0.3 зҡ„зҜҖй»һжЁҷиЁҳиӯҰе‘Ҡпјӣ< 0.1 зҡ„зҜҖй»һеҫһе…¬й–Ӣзҙўеј•з§»йҷӨгҖӮ', 'Every Memory Node carries a composite trust score (0вҖ“1) derived from four dimensions:

| Dimension | Description | Default at creation |
|-----------|-------------|--------------------|
| `accuracy` | Factual correctness | 0.5 |
| `freshness` | Timeliness | 1.0 |
| `utility` | Practical usefulness | 0.5 |
| `author_rep` | Author reputation | 0.5 |

Trust scores are updated continuously by community votes (up/down) and verification counts. Content is SHA-256 signed on every save. Nodes with score < 0.3 are flagged; nodes < 0.1 are removed from the public index.', '{data-model,trust,anti-forgery}', 'public', 'memtrace-spec', '2026-04-11 00:00:00+00', NULL, 'a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3', 'human', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.950, 0.950, 1.000, 0.900, 0.900, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'active', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.memory_nodes (id, schema_version, workspace_id, title_zh, title_en, content_type, content_format, body_zh, body_en, tags, visibility, author, created_at, updated_at, signature, source_type, source_document, extraction_model, copied_from_node, copied_from_ws, trust_score, dim_accuracy, dim_freshness, dim_utility, dim_author_rep, votes_up, votes_down, verifications, traversal_count, unique_traverser_count, status, archived_at, embedding, validity_confirmed_at, validity_confirmed_by, source_file) VALUES ('mem_4c589d76', '1.0', 'ws_spec0001', 'иЁҳжҶ¶зҜҖй»һеүөе»әжҷӮй–“жҲі', 'Memory Node Creation Timestamp', 'factual', 'markdown', '`memory_nodes` иЎЁдёӯзҡ„ `created_at` ж¬„дҪҚйЎһеһӢзӮә TIMESTAMPTZпјҢиЁҳйҢ„иЁҳжҶ¶зҜҖй»һзҡ„еүөе»әжҷӮй–“гҖӮ', 'The `created_at` column in the `memory_nodes` table is of type TIMESTAMPTZ, recording the creation time of the memory node.', '{database,schema,memory_nodes,column,timestamp}', 'public', 'system', '2026-04-24 11:25:39.069241+00', NULL, '6469215e9e84619bfd84e3c3039b487afc9a7f9de83a8e3c6098ba15e5a4ad33', 'ai', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.715, 0.800, 1.000, 0.500, 0.500, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'active', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.memory_nodes (id, schema_version, workspace_id, title_zh, title_en, content_type, content_format, body_zh, body_en, tags, visibility, author, created_at, updated_at, signature, source_type, source_document, extraction_model, copied_from_node, copied_from_ws, trust_score, dim_accuracy, dim_freshness, dim_utility, dim_author_rep, votes_up, votes_down, verifications, traversal_count, unique_traverser_count, status, archived_at, embedding, validity_confirmed_at, validity_confirmed_by, source_file) VALUES ('mem_d005', '1.0', 'ws_spec0001', 'ProvenanceпјҡдҫҶжәҗиҲҮеҸҜжәҜжҖ§', 'Provenance: origin and traceability', 'factual', 'plain', 'жҜҸеҖӢзҜҖй»һзҡ„ provenance зү©д»¶иЁҳйҢ„зҹҘиӯҳзҡ„дҫҶжәҗиіҮиЁҠпјҡauthorпјҲдҪңиҖ…пјүгҖҒcreated_atпјҲе»әз«ӢжҷӮй–“пјүгҖҒsignatureпјҲSHA-256 е…§е®№йӣңж№ҠпјүгҖҒsource_typeпјҲhuman / ai_generated / ai_verifiedпјүгҖӮз·ЁијҜеҫҢж–°еўһ updated_atгҖӮAI иҗғеҸ–зҡ„зҜҖй»һйЎҚеӨ–иЁҳйҢ„ source_documentпјҲдҫҶжәҗж–Үд»¶пјүиҲҮ extraction_modelпјҲдҪҝз”Ёзҡ„ AI жЁЎеһӢпјүгҖӮиӨҮиЈҪеҲ°е…¶д»–зҹҘиӯҳеә«зҡ„зҜҖй»һиЁҳйҢ„ copied_from.node_id иҲҮ copied_from.workspace_idгҖӮProvenance ж°ёйҒ иЁҳйҢ„пјҢдҪҶдёҚж§ӢжҲҗеӯҳеҸ–йҷҗеҲ¶гҖӮ', 'The provenance object on each node records the knowledge''s origin: author, created_at, signature (SHA-256 content hash), source_type (human / ai_generated / ai_verified). updated_at is added on any edit. AI-extracted nodes additionally record source_document (the source file) and extraction_model (the AI model used). Nodes copied across Knowledge Bases record copied_from.node_id and copied_from.workspace_id. Provenance is always recorded but does not restrict access.', '{data-model,provenance,traceability}', 'public', 'memtrace-spec', '2026-04-11 00:00:00+00', NULL, 'b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4', 'human', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.950, 0.950, 1.000, 0.900, 0.900, 0, 0, 0, 2, 2, 'active', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.memory_nodes (id, schema_version, workspace_id, title_zh, title_en, content_type, content_format, body_zh, body_en, tags, visibility, author, created_at, updated_at, signature, source_type, source_document, extraction_model, copied_from_node, copied_from_ws, trust_score, dim_accuracy, dim_freshness, dim_utility, dim_author_rep, votes_up, votes_down, verifications, traversal_count, unique_traverser_count, status, archived_at, embedding, validity_confirmed_at, validity_confirmed_by, source_file) VALUES ('mem_d006', '1.0', 'ws_spec0001', 'Traversal Trackingпјҡиө°иЁӘиЁҲж•ё', 'Traversal Tracking: measuring real usage', 'factual', 'plain', 'зҜҖй»һиҲҮ Edge еҗ„иҮӘиЁҳйҢ„иө°иЁӘж•ёж“ҡгҖӮзҜҖй»һиЁҳйҢ„пјҡtraversal_countпјҲзёҪиө°иЁӘж¬Ўж•ёпјүгҖҒunique_traverser_countпјҲдёҚйҮҚиӨҮиЁӘе®ўж•ёпјүгҖӮEdge иЁҳйҢ„пјҡtraversal_countгҖҒrating_avgпјҲ1вҖ“5 е№іеқҮи©•еҲҶпјҢз„Ўи©•еҲҶжҷӮзӮә nullпјүгҖҒrating_countгҖӮиө°иЁӘйҖҸйҒҺ API зҡ„ POST /nodes/{id}/traverse жҲ– POST /edges/{id}/traverse иЁҳйҢ„гҖӮMCP tool traverse_edge д№ҹжңғи§ёзҷјиЁҲж•ёгҖӮйҖҷдәӣж•ёеӯ—еҸҚжҳ зҹҘиӯҳзҡ„еҜҰйҡӣдҪҝз”Ёй »зҺҮпјҢдёҚеҸӘжҳҜиў«иЁҳйҢ„зҡ„дәӢеҜҰгҖӮ', 'Nodes and edges each track traversal data. Nodes record: traversal_count (total visits) and unique_traverser_count (distinct actors). Edges record: traversal_count, rating_avg (1вҖ“5 average, null if no ratings), and rating_count. Traversals are recorded via POST /nodes/{id}/traverse or POST /edges/{id}/traverse in the REST API, or via the MCP tool traverse_edge. These numbers reflect actual knowledge usage frequency, not just what was recorded.', '{data-model,traversal,usage-tracking}', 'public', 'memtrace-spec', '2026-04-11 00:00:00+00', NULL, 'c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5', 'human', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.950, 0.950, 1.000, 0.900, 0.900, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'active', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.memory_nodes (id, schema_version, workspace_id, title_zh, title_en, content_type, content_format, body_zh, body_en, tags, visibility, author, created_at, updated_at, signature, source_type, source_document, extraction_model, copied_from_node, copied_from_ws, trust_score, dim_accuracy, dim_freshness, dim_utility, dim_author_rep, votes_up, votes_down, verifications, traversal_count, unique_traverser_count, status, archived_at, embedding, validity_confirmed_at, validity_confirmed_by, source_file) VALUES ('mem_d4ea05e2', '1.0', 'ws_spec0001', 'иЁҳжҶ¶зҜҖй»һдҝЎд»»еҲҶж•ё', 'Memory Node Trust Score', 'factual', 'markdown', '`memory_nodes` иЎЁдёӯзҡ„ `trust_score` ж¬„дҪҚйЎһеһӢзӮә NUMERIC(4,3)пјҢиЎЁзӨә 0 еҲ° 1 д№Ӣй–“зҡ„з¶ңеҗҲдҝЎд»»еҲҶж•ёгҖӮ', 'The `trust_score` column in the `memory_nodes` table is of type NUMERIC(4,3), representing a composite trust score between 0 and 1.', '{database,schema,memory_nodes,column,score}', 'public', 'system', '2026-04-24 11:25:39.130605+00', NULL, '7c28f4b6744720099944e0b00fe9f6eacea46d6715cdde3f103aa4ba4cab8d00', 'ai', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.715, 0.800, 1.000, 0.500, 0.500, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'active', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.memory_nodes (id, schema_version, workspace_id, title_zh, title_en, content_type, content_format, body_zh, body_en, tags, visibility, author, created_at, updated_at, signature, source_type, source_document, extraction_model, copied_from_node, copied_from_ws, trust_score, dim_accuracy, dim_freshness, dim_utility, dim_author_rep, votes_up, votes_down, verifications, traversal_count, unique_traverser_count, status, archived_at, embedding, validity_confirmed_at, validity_confirmed_by, source_file) VALUES ('mem_playbook_003', '1.0', 'ws_spec0001', 'жңҖдҪіеҜҰиёҗпјҡеҚҖеҲҶзҜҖй»һйЎһеһӢ', 'Best Practice: Distinguishing Node Types', 'factual', 'markdown', '### е…§е®№йЎһеһӢжҢҮеҚ—
- **дәӢеҜҰжҖ§ (Factual)**пјҡе®ўи§ҖдәӢеҜҰгҖҒжҠҖиЎ“иҰҸж јгҖҒе®ҡзҫ©гҖӮ
- **зЁӢеәҸжҖ§ (Procedural)**пјҡиЎҢеӢ•жӯҘй©ҹгҖҒSOPгҖҒж“ҚдҪңжҢҮеҚ—гҖӮ
- **еҒҸеҘҪжҖ§ (Preference)**пјҡеңҳйҡҠжұәзӯ–гҖҒиЁӯиЁҲеҒҸеҘҪгҖҒйҒёж“ҮзҗҶз”ұгҖӮ
- **иғҢжҷҜжҖ§ (Context)**пјҡе°ҲжЎҲиғҢжҷҜгҖҒй«ҳеұӨж¬Ўе“ІеӯёгҖҒиЁӯиЁҲж„Ҹең–гҖӮ', '### Content Type Guide
- **Factual**: Objective facts, technical specs, definitions.
- **Procedural**: Action steps, SOPs, how-to guides.
- **Preference**: Team decisions, design preferences, rationale for choices.
- **Context**: Project background, high-level philosophy, design intent.', '{best-practice,content-type,guide}', 'public', 'system', '2026-04-24 13:35:31.814382+00', NULL, 'manual_playbook_003', 'ai', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.500, 0.500, 1.000, 0.500, 0.500, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'active', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.memory_nodes (id, schema_version, workspace_id, title_zh, title_en, content_type, content_format, body_zh, body_en, tags, visibility, author, created_at, updated_at, signature, source_type, source_document, extraction_model, copied_from_node, copied_from_ws, trust_score, dim_accuracy, dim_freshness, dim_utility, dim_author_rep, votes_up, votes_down, verifications, traversal_count, unique_traverser_count, status, archived_at, embedding, validity_confirmed_at, validity_confirmed_by, source_file) VALUES ('mem_5b9dd113', '1.0', 'ws_spec0001', 'иЁҳжҶ¶е°ҺеҮәеҠҹиғҪ', 'Memory Export Functionality', 'factual', 'markdown', 'йӣҝиј»оң…?пҶҜоҸ»йҡһдәҷ??е—…?ж’Ңд№©?й–®оҰ·пҲқ?иҮ¬пҠҫ?е”іоҜұ?е”і?зҚўпҺ„ВҖ?Users can export their current working memory to a local file.', 'йӣҝиј»оң…?пҶҜоҸ»йҡһдәҷ??е—…?ж’Ңд№©?й–®оҰ·пҲқ?иҮ¬пҠҫ?е”іоҜұ?е”і?зҚўпҺ„ВҖ?Users can export their current working memory to a local file.', '{memory-management,export}', 'public', 'system', '2026-04-24 11:25:39.214139+00', NULL, 'e642c5361a573c1ec70f8f5f549a951819bcedae6c4c0110291c72e3bde360d4', 'ai', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.715, 0.800, 1.000, 0.500, 0.500, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'active', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.memory_nodes (id, schema_version, workspace_id, title_zh, title_en, content_type, content_format, body_zh, body_en, tags, visibility, author, created_at, updated_at, signature, source_type, source_document, extraction_model, copied_from_node, copied_from_ws, trust_score, dim_accuracy, dim_freshness, dim_utility, dim_author_rep, votes_up, votes_down, verifications, traversal_count, unique_traverser_count, status, archived_at, embedding, validity_confirmed_at, validity_confirmed_by, source_file) VALUES ('mem_g001', '1.0', 'ws_spec0001', 'DecayпјҡEdge ж¬ҠйҮҚзҡ„иҮӘз„¶иЎ°жёӣ', 'Decay: natural weight reduction on edges', 'factual', 'markdown', 'Edge ж¬ҠйҮҚйҡЁжҷӮй–“дҫқд»ҘдёӢе…¬ејҸиЎ°жёӣпјҲv1пјүпјҡ

```
weight(t) = wвӮҖ Г— 0.5 ^ (days_since_last_access / half_life)
```

**ж ёеҝғеҺҹеүҮ**пјҡ**Decay еЎ‘йҖ жіЁж„ҸеҠӣпјҢдёҚеЎ‘йҖ еӯҳеңЁ**гҖӮжІ’жңүжқұиҘҝеӣ  decay иҖҢиў«еҲӘйҷӨгҖӮ

**Edge зӢҖж…ӢиҪүжҸӣ**пјҡз•¶ `weight < min_weight`пјҲй җиЁӯ 0.1пјүпјҢEdge йҖІе…Ҙ `faded` зӢҖж…Ӣпјҡ
- еҫһй җиЁӯ Graph View иҲҮ traversal зөҗжһңйҡұи—Ҹ
- д»Қеӯҳж–јиіҮж–ҷеә«пјҲ`status = ''faded''`пјүпјҢеҸҜз”ұеҺҹдҪңиҖ…жҲ– admin йӮ„еҺҹ
- API еҠ  `include_faded=true` д»ҚеҸҜжҹҘи©ў

**зҜҖй»һеұӨзҙҡ**пјҡ
- `evergreen` е·ҘдҪңеҚҖпјҡзҜҖй»һжң¬иә«дҫқгҖҢи§ҖеҜҹжңҹе…§иө°иЁӘиЁҲж•ёгҖҚжӯёжӘ”пјҲВ§7.3пјүпјҢдёҚеҸ—жҷӮй–“иЎ°жёӣ
- `ephemeral` е·ҘдҪңеҚҖпјҡз•¶жүҖжңүзӣёйҖЈ Edge зҡҶ fadedпјҢзҜҖй»һиҮӘеӢ• archived

**Pinned дҫӢеӨ–**пјҡ`pinned: true` зҡ„зҜҖй»һиҲҮ Edge е®Ңе…ЁиұҒе…Қж–јиЎ°жёӣиҲҮиЁҲж•ёжӯёжӘ”гҖӮ

иЎ°жёӣи§ёзҷјпјҡжҜҸж—Ҙз”ұ `apply_edge_decay()` SQL еҮҪејҸеҹ·иЎҢпјҲйҸЎе°„ `packages/core/src/decay.ts`пјүгҖӮ', 'Edge weight decays over time according to (v1):

```
weight(t) = wвӮҖ Г— 0.5 ^ (days_since_last_access / half_life)
```

**Core principle**: **Decay shapes attention, not existence.** Nothing is deleted by decay alone.

**Edge state transition**: When `weight < min_weight` (default 0.1), the edge transitions to `faded`:
- Hidden from default Graph View and traversal results
- Still stored in the database (`status = ''faded''`); restorable by the original author or admin
- Queryable via API with `include_faded=true`

**Node level**:
- `evergreen` workspace: nodes are archived based on traversal count within an observation window (В§7.3), not time-based
- `ephemeral` workspace: when all connected edges are faded, the node is auto-archived

**Pinned exemption**: Nodes and edges with `pinned: true` are fully exempt from both time-decay and traversal-count archiving.

Trigger: daily by the `apply_edge_decay()` SQL function (mirrors `packages/core/src/decay.ts`).', '{graph-mechanics,decay,weight,faded,archive}', 'public', 'memtrace-spec', '2026-04-11 00:00:00+00', NULL, 'd5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6', 'human', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.950, 0.950, 1.000, 0.950, 0.900, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'active', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.memory_nodes (id, schema_version, workspace_id, title_zh, title_en, content_type, content_format, body_zh, body_en, tags, visibility, author, created_at, updated_at, signature, source_type, source_document, extraction_model, copied_from_node, copied_from_ws, trust_score, dim_accuracy, dim_freshness, dim_utility, dim_author_rep, votes_up, votes_down, verifications, traversal_count, unique_traverser_count, status, archived_at, embedding, validity_confirmed_at, validity_confirmed_by, source_file) VALUES ('mem_g002', '1.0', 'ws_spec0001', 'Co-Access Boostпјҡе…ұеӯҳеҸ–еҠ жҲҗ', 'Co-Access Boost: strengthening edges through use', 'factual', 'markdown', 'з•¶е…©еҖӢзӣёйҖЈзҜҖй»һеңЁеҗҢдёҖжғ…еўғдёӢиў«еҫӘеәҸжҲ–еҗҢжҷӮеӯҳеҸ–пјҲCo-AccessпјүпјҢе°ҚжҮү Edge зҡ„ weight жңғеҫ—еҲ°еҠ жҲҗпјҢеҠ жҲҗйҮҸдҫқ relation type иҖҢз•°пјҡ

| Relation | Boost |
|----------|-------|
| `depends_on` | +0.30 |
| `extends` | +0.20 |
| `related_to` | +0.15 |
| `contradicts` | +0.10 |

еҗҢжҷӮи§ёзҷјпјҡco_access_count +1гҖҒlast_co_accessed жӣҙж–°гҖҒweight дёҠйҷҗ 1.0гҖӮAPI и·Ҝеҫ‘ POST /edges/{id}/traverse жҲ– MCP tool traverse_edge зҡҶжңғи§ёзҷј co-access boostгҖӮ', 'When two connected nodes are accessed sequentially or simultaneously in the same context (Co-Access), the corresponding edge''s weight receives a boost based on relation type:

| Relation | Boost |
|----------|-------|
| `depends_on` | +0.30 |
| `extends` | +0.20 |
| `related_to` | +0.15 |
| `contradicts` | +0.10 |

Also increments co_access_count, updates last_co_accessed, and caps weight at 1.0. Triggered by POST /edges/{id}/traverse or MCP tool traverse_edge.', '{graph-mechanics,co-access,boost,weight}', 'public', 'memtrace-spec', '2026-04-11 00:00:00+00', NULL, 'e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7a2b3c4d5e6f7', 'human', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.950, 0.950, 1.000, 0.950, 0.900, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'active', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
